tourBios.curYrHigh: Earned PGA TOUR Latinoamérica conditional status by finishing T15 at the Bogota, Colombia Q-School in January.
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T66 at the European Tour's Joburg Open in South Africa... Missed the cut at both the Sunshine Tour's Dimension Data Pro-Am and the Web.com Tour's Chitimacha Louisiana Open.

2014: Earned PGA TOUR Latinoamérica conditional status by finishing T21 at the Sebring, Florida Q-School in January... Finished his first PGA TOUR Latinoamérica season ranked 74th on the Order of Merit after making the cut in 5 of his 11 starts. Put together four rounds under par to stay inside the top 5 throughout the entire week and finish T5 at the Dominican Republic Open played at Casa de Campo's famous Teeth of the Dog golf course in May... Had two top-25s. First came in at the Stella Artois Open in Guatemala, a T25...Added a T21 at the 83 Abierto OSDE del Centro in Cordoba, Argentina. Was tied for fifth with 18 holes to play before a final-round 76 dropped him down the leaderboard.

2013: Made first career start on the Web.com Tour at Colombia Championship (missed cut).

2012: Played in two European Challenge Tour tournaments, missing the cut in both. 

2011: Turned professional in May.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was the 2009 Florida Junior Tour Champion, winning by seven strokes with a score of 207...Carded three top-20 AJGA finishes in 2009, with a scoring average of 72.6…Golf letterman in his first two years of high school at St. Stephen's Episcopal School...At Manatee High School, was the No. 1 player all four years of his high school career.
tourBios.personal: Son of Hall of Famer Tony Jacklin, champion of the 1969 British Open and the 1970 U.S. Open… Has five brothers and sisters... Attended the University of North Carolina in Chapel Hill for a year, before turning pro… Attended Manatee High School… His hobbies include paddleboarding and working out... Twitter name is @seanjacklin... Instagram name is @sjacklin91
